# Inventory System Patterns

Skill for implementing inventory systems including items, combination, drag-and-drop, keycards, and equipment in SCPB.

## When to Use

Use this skill when:
- Implementing inventory functionality
- Adding new items to the game
- Creating item combinations
- Managing equipment slots
- Handling keycard access
- Debugging inventory issues

## Inventory Structure

```blitzbasic
; Inventory constants
Const MAX_INVENTORY_SLOTS% = 9
Const MAX_EQUIPMENT_SLOTS% = 4

Const EQUIP_NONE% = 0
Const EQUIP_NVG% = 0
Const EQUIP_GAS_MASK% = 1
Const EQUIP_HEADLAMP% = 2
Const EQUIP_ARMOR% = 3

; Item categories
Const ITEM_CATEGORY_GENERAL% = 0
Const ITEM_CATEGORY_KEYCARD% = 1
Const ITEM_CATEGORY_MEDICAL% = 2
Const ITEM_CATEGORY_EQUIPMENT% = 3
Const ITEM_CATEGORY_CONSUMABLE% = 4

; Inventory type
Type Inventory
    Field Slots[MAX_INVENTORY_SLOTS]  ; Item IDs
    Field SelectedSlot%               ; Currently selected
    Field Equipment[EQUIP_ARMOR]      ; Equipped items
    Field Capacity%                   ; Max slots
    Field Weight#                     ; Current weight
    Field MaxWeight#                  ; Max weight
End Type

Global PlayerInventory.Inventory
```

## Item Definition

```blitzbasic
; Item type
Type Items
    Field obj%              ; 3D object in world
    Field ItemID%           ; Unique item instance ID
    Field Type%             ; Item type constant
    Field Name$
    Field Description$
    Field Category%
    Field Icon$             ; Icon texture
    Field Mesh$             ; World mesh
    Field State%            ; 0=normal, 1=used, 2=combined
    Field State2%           ; Secondary state (durability, charges)
    Field Quantity%         ; Stackable items
    Field MaxQuantity%      ; Max stack size
End Type

; Item constants
Const ITEM_NONE% = 0
Const ITEM_MEDKIT% = 1
Const ITEM_BANDAGE% = 2
Const ITEM_BATTERY% = 3
Const ITEM_FLASHLIGHT% = 4
Const ITEM_WORKING_FLASHLIGHT% = 5
Const ITEM_KEYCARD_RED% = 10
Const ITEM_KEYCARD_BLUE% = 11
Const ITEM_KEYCARD_GREEN% = 12
Const ITEM_KEYCARD_OMEGA% = 13
Const ITEM_2999_BEVERAGE% = 20
```

## Inventory Management

### Create Inventory

```blitzbasic
Function CreateInventory%()
    inv.Inventory = New Inventory
    inv\Capacity = MAX_INVENTORY_SLOTS
    inv\SelectedSlot = 0
    inv\MaxWeight = 50.0

    ; Initialize slots
    For i = 0 To MAX_INVENTORY_SLOTS - 1
        inv\Slots[i] = ITEM_NONE
    Next

    ; Initialize equipment
    For i = 0 To MAX_EQUIPMENT_SLOTS - 1
        inv\Equipment[i] = ITEM_NONE
    Next

    Return Handle(inv)
End Function
```

### Add Item

```blitzbasic
Function Inventory_AddItem%(inv.Inventory, itemType%, quantity% = 1)
    If inv = Null Then Return False

    ; Check for existing stack
    If IsStackable(itemType)
        For i = 0 To inv\Capacity - 1
            If inv\Slots[i] = itemType
                item.Items = GetItemAtSlot(i)
                If item\Quantity < item\MaxQuantity
                    item\Quantity = item\Quantity + quantity
                    Return True
                End If
            End If
        Next
    End If

    ; Find empty slot
    For i = 0 To inv\Capacity - 1
        If inv\Slots[i] = ITEM_NONE
            inv\Slots[i] = itemType
            CreateInventoryItem(i, itemType, quantity)
            Return True
        End If
    Next

    ; Inventory full
    Return False
End Function

Function IsStackable%(itemType%)
    Select itemType
        Case ITEM_BATTERY
        Case ITEM_BANDAGE
        Case ITEM_2999_BEVERAGE
            Return True
        Default
            Return False
    End Select
End Function
```

### Remove Item

```blitzbasic
Function Inventory_RemoveItem%(inv.Inventory, itemType%, quantity% = 1)
    If inv = Null Then Return False

    ; Find item
    For i = 0 To inv\Capacity - 1
        If inv\Slots[i] = itemType
            item.Items = GetItemAtSlot(i)
            If item\Quantity > quantity
                item\Quantity = item\Quantity - quantity
            Else
                FreeItem(item)
                inv\Slots[i] = ITEM_NONE
            End If
            Return True
        End If
    Next

    Return False
End Function

Function Inventory_RemoveAtSlot%(inv.Inventory, slot%)
    If slot < 0 Or slot >= inv\Capacity Then Return False

    item.Items = GetItemAtSlot(slot)
    If item <> Null
        FreeItem(item)
        inv\Slots[slot] = ITEM_NONE
        Return True
    End If

    Return False
End Function
```

### Query Inventory

```blitzbasic
Function Inventory_HasItem%(inv.Inventory, itemType%)
    If inv = Null Then Return False

    For i = 0 To inv\Capacity - 1
        If inv\Slots[i] = itemType
            Return True
        End If
    Next

    Return False
End Function

Function Inventory_GetItemCount%(inv.Inventory, itemType%)
    count% = 0

    For i = 0 To inv\Capacity - 1
        If inv\Slots[i] = itemType
            item.Items = GetItemAtSlot(i)
            count = count + item\Quantity
        End If
    Next

    Return count
End Function

Function Inventory_IsFull%(inv.Inventory)
    For i = 0 To inv\Capacity - 1
        If inv\Slots[i] = ITEM_NONE
            Return False
        End If
    Next
    Return True
End Function

Function Inventory_GetFirstEmptySlot%(inv.Inventory)
    For i = 0 To inv\Capacity - 1
        If inv\Slots[i] = ITEM_NONE
            Return i
        End If
    Next
    Return -1
End Function
```

## Item Combination

```blitzbasic
; Combination table
Type Combination
    Field Item1%
    Field Item2%
    Field Result%
End Type

Global Combinations[50]

Function InitCombinations()
    ; Define combinations
    AddCombination(ITEM_BATTERY, ITEM_FLASHLIGHT, ITEM_WORKING_FLASHLIGHT)
    AddCombination(ITEM_MEDKIT, ITEM_BANDAGE, ITEM_ADVANCED_MEDKIT)
    AddCombination(ITEM_KEYCARD_RED, ITEM_KEYCARD_BLUE, ITEM_KEYCARD_GREEN)
End Function

Function AddCombination%(item1%, item2%, result%)
    For i = 0 To 49
        If Combinations[i]\Item1 = 0
            Combinations[i]\Item1 = item1
            Combinations[i]\Item2 = item2
            Combinations[i]\Result = result
            Return True
        End If
    Next
    Return False
End Function

Function CanCombine%(item1%, item2%)
    For i = 0 To 49
        If (Combinations[i]\Item1 = item1 And Combinations[i]\Item2 = item2) Or _
           (Combinations[i]\Item1 = item2 And Combinations[i]\Item2 = item1)
            Return True
        End If
    Next
    Return False
End Function

Function GetCombinationResult%(item1%, item2%)
    For i = 0 To 49
        If (Combinations[i]\Item1 = item1 And Combinations[i]\Item2 = item2) Or _
           (Combinations[i]\Item1 = item2 And Combinations[i]\Item2 = item1)
            Return Combinations[i]\Result
        End If
    Next
    Return ITEM_NONE
End Function
```

### Perform Combination

```blitzbasic
Function Inventory_Combine%(inv.Inventory, slot1%, slot2%)
    item1.Items = GetItemAtSlot(slot1)
    item2.Items = GetItemAtSlot(slot2)

    If item1 = Null Or item2 = Null Then Return False

    result% = GetCombinationResult(item1\Type, item2\Type)

    If result <> ITEM_NONE
        ; Remove both items
        Inventory_RemoveAtSlot(inv, slot1)
        Inventory_RemoveAtSlot(inv, slot2)

        ; Add result
        Inventory_AddItem(inv, result)

        ; Play sound
        PlaySound("sfx/combine.wav")

        ; Show message
        ShowMessage("Combined: " + ItemName(result))

        Return True
    End If

    Return False
End Function
```

## Drag and Drop

```blitzbasic
; Drag state
Global DRAG_SLOT% = -1
Global DRAG_ITEM% = 0
Global DRAG_START_X% = 0
Global DRAG_START_Y% = 0

Function Inventory_StartDrag%(slot%, x%, y%)
    If slot < 0 Or slot >= MAX_INVENTORY_SLOTS Then Return False

    itemType = PlayerInventory\Slots[slot]
    If itemType = ITEM_NONE Then Return False

    DRAG_SLOT = slot
    DRAG_ITEM = itemType
    DRAG_START_X = x
    DRAG_START_Y = y

    Return True
End Function

Function Inventory_UpdateDrag%(x%, y%)
    ; Update drag position
    ; Render drag preview
End Function

Function Inventory_EndDrag%(dropSlot%)
    If DRAG_SLOT < 0 Then Return False

    ; Same slot = deselect
    If dropSlot = DRAG_SLOT
        DRAG_SLOT = -1
        DRAG_ITEM = 0
        Return True
    End If

    ; Empty slot = move
    If PlayerInventory\Slots[dropSlot] = ITEM_NONE
        PlayerInventory\Slots[dropSlot] = PlayerInventory\Slots[DRAG_SLOT]
        PlayerInventory\Slots[DRAG_SLOT] = ITEM_NONE
    ; Occupied slot = swap
    Else
        temp = PlayerInventory\Slots[dropSlot]
        PlayerInventory\Slots[dropSlot] = PlayerInventory\Slots[DRAG_SLOT]
        PlayerInventory\Slots[DRAG_SLOT] = temp
    End If

    DRAG_SLOT = -1
    DRAG_ITEM = 0

    Return True
End Function
```

## Keycard System

```blitzbasic
; Keycard levels
Const KEY_NONE% = 0
Const KEY_RED% = 1
Const KEY_BLUE% = 2
Const KEY_GREEN% = 3
Const KEY_OMEGA% = 4

Function Inventory_HasKeycard%(inv.Inventory, level%)
    Select level
        Case KEY_RED
            Return inv\Slots[ContainsItem(ITEM_KEYCARD_RED)] <> ITEM_NONE
        Case KEY_BLUE
            Return inv\Slots[ContainsItem(ITEM_KEYCARD_BLUE)] <> ITEM_NONE
        Case KEY_GREEN
            Return inv\Slots[ContainsItem(ITEM_KEYCARD_GREEN)] <> ITEM_NONE
        Case KEY_OMEGA
            Return inv\Slots[ContainsItem(ITEM_KEYCARD_OMEGA)] <> ITEM_NONE Or _
                   (inv\Slots[ContainsItem(ITEM_KEYCARD_RED)] <> ITEM_NONE And _
                    inv\Slots[ContainsItem(ITEM_KEYCARD_BLUE)] <> ITEM_NONE And _
                    inv\Slots[ContainsItem(ITEM_KEYCARD_GREEN)] <> ITEM_NONE)
    End Select
    Return False
End Function

Function Door_RequiresKeycard%(doorType%)
    Select doorType
        Case DOOR_STANDARD
            Return KEY_NONE
        Case DOOR_CHECKPOINT
            Return KEY_BLUE
        Case DOOR_HEAVY
            Return KEY_RED
        Case DOOR_OMEGA
            Return KEY_GREEN
        Case DOOR_ELEVATOR_HCZ
            Return KEY_RED
        Case DOOR_ELEVATOR_EZ
            Return KEY_GREEN
        Default
            Return KEY_NONE
    End Select
End Function

Function Door_TryOpen%(doorType%)
    required = Door_RequiresKeycard(doorType)

    If required = KEY_NONE
        Return True
    End If

    If Inventory_HasKeycard(PlayerInventory, required)
        Return True
    End If

    ; Show access denied
    ShowAccessDenied(required)
    Return False
End Function
```

## Equipment System

```blitzbasic
Function Inventory_Equip%(inv.Inventory, slot%)
    itemType = inv\Slots[slot]
    If itemType = ITEM_NONE Then Return False

    ; Check if equippable
    equipSlot = GetEquipmentSlot(itemType)
    If equipSlot < 0 Then Return False

    ; Unequip current
    If inv\Equipment[equipSlot] <> ITEM_NONE
        UnequipItem(inv, equipSlot)
    End If

    ; Equip new
    inv\Equipment[equipSlot] = itemType
    RemoveFromInventory(inv, itemType, 1)

    ; Apply effects
    ApplyEquipmentEffects(equipSlot, True)

    PlaySound("sfx/equip.wav")
    Return True
End Function

Function Inventory_Unequip%(inv.Inventory, equipSlot%)
    itemType = inv\Equipment[equipSlot]
    If itemType = ITEM_NONE Then Return False

    ; Check for space
    If Inventory_IsFull(inv)
        ShowMessage("Inventory full!")
        Return False
    End If

    ; Remove effects
    ApplyEquipmentEffects(equipSlot, False)

    ; Add back to inventory
    inv\Equipment[equipSlot] = ITEM_NONE
    Inventory_AddItem(inv, itemType)

    PlaySound("sfx/unequip.wav")
    Return True
End Function

Function GetEquipmentSlot%(itemType%)
    Select itemType
        Case ITEM_NVG
            Return EQUIP_NVG
        Case ITEM_GAS_MASK
            Return EQUIP_GAS_MASK
        Case ITEM_HEADLAMP
            Return EQUIP_HEADLAMP
        Case ITEM_LIGHT_ARMOR
            Return EQUIP_ARMOR
        Default
            Return -1
    End Select
End Function

Function ApplyEquipmentEffects%(equipSlot%, equip%)
    Select equipSlot
        Case EQUIP_NVG
            SetNightVision(equip)
        Case EQUIP_GAS_MASK
            SetGasMask(equip)
        Case EQUIP_HEADLAMP
            SetHeadlamp(equip)
        Case EQUIP_ARMOR
            SetArmor(equip)
    End Select
End Function
```

## Item Use

```blitzbasic
Function Inventory_UseItem%(inv.Inventory, slot%)
    itemType = inv\Slots[slot]
    If itemType = ITEM_NONE Then Return False

    Select itemType
        Case ITEM_MEDKIT
            UseMedkit()
        Case ITEM_BANDAGE
            UseBandage()
        Case ITEM_FLASHLIGHT
            ToggleFlashlight()
        Case ITEM_WORKING_FLASHLIGHT
            ToggleFlashlight()
        Case ITEM_2999_BEVERAGE
            UseBeverage()
    End Select

    ; Consumable items
    If IsConsumable(itemType)
        Inventory_RemoveAtSlot(inv, slot)
    End If

    Return True
End Function

Function UseMedkit()
    HealAmount# = 50.0
    If PlayerHealth < 100
        PlayerHealth = Min(PlayerHealth + HealAmount, 100)
        PlaySound("sfx/use_medkit.wav")
        ShowMessage("Healed for " + Int(HealAmount))
    End If
End Function

Function UseBandage()
    If Bleeding > 0
        Bleeding = 0
        PlaySound("sfx/use_bandage.wav")
        ShowMessage("Bandage applied")
    End If
End Function

Function ToggleFlashlight()
    If FlashlightOn
        FlashlightOn = False
        ShowMessage("Flashlight OFF")
    Else
        If HasItem(ITEM_WORKING_FLASHLIGHT)
            FlashlightOn = True
            ShowMessage("Flashlight ON")
        Else
            ShowMessage("No working flashlight!")
        End If
    End If
End Function
```

## Inventory UI

```blitzbasic
Function RenderInventoryUI()
    ; Draw inventory slots
    For i = 0 To MAX_INVENTORY_SLOTS - 1
        x = INVENTORY_START_X + i * SLOT_SIZE
        y = INVENTORY_START_Y

        ; Draw slot background
        DrawSlot(x, y, SLOT_SIZE, (i = PlayerInventory\SelectedSlot))

        ; Draw item if present
        itemType = PlayerInventory\Slots[i]
        If itemType <> ITEM_NONE
            DrawItemIcon(x, y, itemType)
        End If

        ; Draw quantity if stackable
        item.Items = GetItemAtSlot(i)
        If item\Quantity > 1
            DrawQuantity(x, y, item\Quantity)
        End If
    Next

    ; Draw equipment slots
    For i = 0 To MAX_EQUIPMENT_SLOTS - 1
        x = EQUIP_START_X
        y = EQUIP_START_Y + i * SLOT_SIZE

        DrawSlot(x, y, SLOT_SIZE, False)

        itemType = PlayerInventory\Equipment[i]
        If itemType <> ITEM_NONE
            DrawItemIcon(x, y, itemType)
        End If
    Next

    ; Draw drag preview
    If DRAG_SLOT >= 0
        DrawDragPreview()
    End If

    ; Draw tooltip
    DrawItemTooltip()
End Function
```

## Quick Reference

| Function | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `Inventory_AddItem(inv, type, qty)` | Add item to inventory |
| `Inventory_RemoveItem(inv, type)` | Remove item from inventory |
| `Inventory_HasItem(inv, type)` | Check if has item |
| `Inventory_Combine(inv, slot1, slot2)` | Combine two items |
| `Inventory_Equip(inv, slot)` | Equip item from inventory |
| `Inventory_UseItem(inv, slot)` | Use item in slot |
| `Inventory_HasKeycard(inv, level)` | Check for keycard |
| `Inventory_IsFull(inv)` | Check if inventory full |
